This paper proposes a method for improving accuracy in restricted domains while preventing overfitting and aggressive model compression and acceleration. The paper focuses on deep learning models for detection and tracking, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses the trade-off between compression and generalization, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to video data sets, which are commonly studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.RO.
